---
---

<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Mosaigo — Composable Pipeline Engine for Go</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Mosaigo is an open-source pipeline engine for Go. Compose typed, self-describing steps into pipelines for any domain: data processing, computer vision, IoT, audio, or anything that flows."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href="/images/favicon-32x32.png" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="16x16" href="/images/favicon-16x16.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/images/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/landing.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav class="topnav">
      <a href="/" class="topnav-logo">
        <img src="/images/mozzy-icon.webp" alt="mosaigo" />
        mosaigo
      </a>
    </nav>

    <section class="hero" style="padding: 90px 24px 24px;">
      <div class="hero-badge"><span class="dot"></span> Open source &middot; Pure Go</div>
      <h1>Turn small steps into a <span class="accent">big vision</span></h1>
      <p class="tagline" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Mosaigo (mosaic-go) is a composable pipeline engine for Go that handles the hard parts so you can focus on what matters.</p>
      <img src="/images/mozzy1.webp" alt="Mozzy, the Mosaigo mascot" style="max-width: 300px; margin: 24px auto 0; display: block;" />
      <p class="section-desc" style="margin: 12px auto 0; text-align:center; max-width:580px;">
        Processing complex data at high throughput with low latency gets hard fast. Resource lifecycles need to happen outside the hot path. Parallel routines need to communicate without blocking. The plumbing grows until it drowns the actual logic.
      </p>
      <p class="section-desc" style="margin: 16px auto 0; text-align:center; max-width:580px;">
        Mosaigo takes a different approach. Single-purpose steps that each do one thing, composed into pipelines through configuration or at runtime. Strong typing across every boundary cuts boilerplate, removes repetition, and catches mismatches before anything runs. Steps describe themselves with a small set of metadata, making them discoverable, configurable, and reusable out of the box.
      </p>
      <p class="section-desc" style="margin: 16px auto 0; text-align:center; max-width:580px;">
        Because steps are cheap to write and swap, you can try three approaches instead of committing to one. Built-in observability means you can measure and compare them empirically, not guess. The framework is designed for fast iteration: change a step, reconfigure a pipeline, see what works, keep the winner.
      </p>
      <p class="section-desc" style="margin: 16px auto 0; text-align:center; max-width:580px;">
        We're building it right now.
      </p>

      <div style="margin: 40px auto 0; max-width: 420px;">
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px;">Stay in the loop</h3>
        <form
          id="signup-form"
          action="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfN7C3Q2BmUPWx5H0oMtXJGqnf1ijtFr2K4dX0r8FXeF2CGww/formResponse"
          method="POST"
        >
          <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px;">
            <input
              type="text"
              name="entry.222938406"
              placeholder="Name"
              required
              style="padding: 10px 14px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--bg-card); color: var(--text); font-size: 0.92rem; font-family: inherit; outline: none;"
            />
            <input
              type="email"
              name="entry.649963799"
              placeholder="Email"
              required
              style="padding: 10px 14px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--bg-card); color: var(--text); font-size: 0.92rem; font-family: inherit; outline: none;"
            />
            <button
              type="submit"
              style="padding: 11px 24px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--primary); background: var(--primary); color: #fff; font-size: 0.92rem; font-weight: 600; font-family: inherit; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s;"
            >
              Notify me
            </button>
          </div>
        </form>
        <p id="signup-thanks" style="display:none; margin-top: 12px; color: var(--success); font-size: 0.88rem;">
          Thanks! We'll keep you posted.
        </p>
        <p id="signup-error" style="display:none; margin-top: 12px; color: #e55; font-size: 0.88rem;"></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="footer">
      <p>&copy; 2025-present mosaigoio contributors</p>
    </footer>
    <script is:inline>
      document.getElementById('signup-form').addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
        e.preventDefault();
        var form = this;
        var btn = form.querySelector('button[type="submit"]');
        var errorEl = document.getElementById('signup-error');
        var thanksEl = document.getElementById('signup-thanks');
        var name = form.querySelector('[name="entry.222938406"]').value.trim();
        var email = form.querySelector('[name="entry.649963799"]').value.trim();

        errorEl.style.display = 'none';
        errorEl.textContent = '';

        // Client-side validation
        if (!name) {
          errorEl.textContent = 'Please enter your name.';
          errorEl.style.display = 'block';
          return;
        }
        if (!email || !/^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/.test(email)) {
          errorEl.textContent = 'Please enter a valid email address.';
          errorEl.style.display = 'block';
          return;
        }

        btn.disabled = true;
        btn.textContent = 'Sending\u2026';

        var data = new URLSearchParams(new FormData(form));
        fetch(form.action, {
          method: 'POST',
          mode: 'no-cors',
          headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' },
          body: data.toString()
        }).then(function() {
          form.style.display = 'none';
          thanksEl.style.display = 'block';
        }).catch(function(err) {
          btn.disabled = false;
          btn.textContent = 'Notify me';
          errorEl.textContent = 'Something went wrong — please try again.';
          errorEl.style.display = 'block';
          console.error('Form submission error:', err);
        });
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
